ents", "obj": "species", "prob": 0.9882689714431763, "span": {"begin": 755, "end": 763}}, {"id": ["mesh:D014652"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "vascular damage", "obj": "disease", "prob": 0.9963226318359375, "span": {"begin": 776, "end": 791}}, {"id": ["mesh:D007249"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "neutrophil infiltration", "obj": "disease", "prob": 0.9596439003944397, "span": {"begin": 796, "end": 819}}, {"id": ["CL:0000115"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "Endothelial cell", "obj": "cell_type", "prob": 0.8240585327148438, "span": {"begin": 869, "end": 885}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:3827"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "bradykinin", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9802573323249817, "span": {"begin": 900, "end": 910}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:3569"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "IL6", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9750466346740723, "span": {"begin": 1029, "end": 1032}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:3627"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "CXCL10", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.8828182816505432, "span": {"begin": 1034, "end": 1040}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:7124"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "TNF", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9820005297660828, "span": {"begin": 1042, "end": 1045}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "CD4", "obj": "cell_type", "prob": 0.4419473111629486, "span": {"begin": 1076, "end": 1079}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:920"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "CD4+", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9754619598388672, "span": {"begin": 1076, "end": 1080}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:925"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "CD8+", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9908437728881836, "span": {"begin": 1085, "end": 1089}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "monocytes", "obj": "cell_type", "prob": 0.7152621746063232, "span": {"begin": 1116, "end": 1125}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "plasmablast-like neutrophils", "obj": "cell_type", "prob": 0.8038312196731567, "span": {"begin": 1137, "end": 1165}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "eosinophils", "obj": "cell_type", "prob": 0.7410523891448975, "span": {"begin": 1170, "end": 1181}}, {"id": ["mesh:D007249"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "hyperinflammatory", "obj": "disease", "prob": 0.9147586822509766, "span": {"begin": 1202, "end": 1219}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:3569"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "IL-6", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9834364652633667, "span": {"begin": 1265, "end": 1269}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:3827"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "bradykinin", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9890491962432861, "span": {"begin": 1284, "end": 1294}}, {"id": ["mesh:D007249"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "hyperinflammation", "obj": "disease", "prob": 0.9998899698257446, "span": {"begin": 1351, "end": 1368}}], "text": "Bradykinin (BK) plays an important role in the kinin-kallikrein system (KKS) as a regulator of blood pressure and can induce vasodilation, increase blood flow, as well as hypotension. BK is also an important part of the inflammatory process after injury, inducing pain stimulation, and increased vascular permeability (Maas, 10.1007/s12016-016-8540-0). The bradykinin system gets activated through various methods, including nanoparticles and SARS-COV-2 via the contact activation system (Maas, 10.1007/s12016-016-8540-0).  Activation of the bradykinin system increases production of bradykinin. Bradykinin increases vascular permeability and activates endothelial cells(Garvin 2020 doi: 10.7554/eLife.59177). Vascular permeability is present in covid-19 patients with severe vascular damage and neutrophil infiltration (Carvalho 2021 doi: 10.1038/s41577-021-00522-1). Endothelial cell activation by bradykinin causes loss of anti-inflammatory properties and recruitment of&nbsp; proinflammatory mediators such as an increase in IL6, CXCL10, TNF as well as hyperactivation of CD4+ and CD8+, and increased numbers of monocytes, including plasmablast-like neutrophils and eosinophils, all hallmarks of a hyperinflammatory state (Bernard 2020 doi: 10.3390/v13010029). IL-6, activated by bradykinin&rsquo;s activation of the endothelium, also exacerbates hyperinflammation.", "timestamp": "Mon Jun 08 15:34:47 +0000 2026"}